sentences: === 2005–present: Return to music ===
In 2005, she returned with "L.O.V. E", produced by DJ Mickey Bono of the Beat Thrillerz.
In spring 2007, Rockell recorded the single "Playin' My Love".
It was released to Dance/Rhythmic format radio in July 2007.
A freestyle remix by Salsation 3 was released in November 2007.
On June 3, 2009, Rockell released the duet single "When I Want You Back" with Joe Zangie.
In 2012, Rockell signed a new management deal with BlackCole Entertainment.
"I Fell In Love" peaked at #61 on the Billboard Hot 100 in early 1997.
"In a Dream", the follow-up to "I Fell In Love", peaked at #72 on the Billboard Hot 100 in June, 1998.
"Can't We Try" with Collage peaked at #59 on the Billboard Hot 100 in 1998.
"When I'm Gone" failed to chart on the Billboard Hot 100 in 1999, but appeared on the Hot Dance Airplay and Hot Dance Music/Club Play charts.

“When I Want You Back” was previously recorded by Wendy.
Later in June, she released a dance cover of Donna Summer's "On the Radio".
On December 11 of that year, she released her single "Turn Up the Heat" which had a new sound of freestyle and dance-pop from her previous works.
It hit the #1 spot on the Canadian Singles Chart during that year, making it the most successful freestyle dance music single of the decade in Canada.
